<h2 id="475">10. Linking variations to a Mediamarkt catalogue category</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>After you created a marketplace format for Mediamarkt with the <strong>Mediamarkt</strong> assistant or manually, the property <strong>Mediamarkt</strong> is created in your plentymarkets system. A new selection value is added to the <strong>Mediamarkt category group</strong> property for each category selected in the <strong>Settings</strong> step of the assistant. In order for your variations to be exported in the appropriate catalogue, they have to be linked to the <strong>Mediamarkt category group</strong> property in the <strong>Properties</strong> tab of a variation.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Linking a variation to a category:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item » [Open item]</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Variations</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the variation that should be linked.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Properties</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Variation properties</strong> area, select the property <strong>Mediamarkt category group</strong> from the <strong>Properties</strong> drop-down list and click on <strong>Add</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus-square  "></i></span>).<br>
→ The property is added.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the desired category group from the <strong>Value</strong> drop-down list for the <strong>Mediamarkt category group</strong> property.<br>
→ The variation will be exported in this catalogue.<br>
<strong><em>Example:</em>*If you pick the value *VIDEO CASSETTES</strong>, the catalogue variation is exported for the <strong>VIDEO CASSETTES</strong> category.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Repeat steps 5 and 6 for all categories where you want to offer the variation.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_linking_properties_with_variations_and_saving_values">10.1. Linking properties with variations and saving values</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>All properties, sales prices and barcodes that you have created for mapping them in the catalogue now need to be linked to the variations that you want to export to the market. This is described on the <strong>Item</strong> pages of the manual:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Learn how to link properties to variations in the <a href="/en/item/managing-items#4800">Linking properties and saving a value</a> chapter.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Learn how to link sales prices to variations in the <a href="/en/item/managing-items#240">Linking sales prices</a> chapter.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Learn how to link barcodes to variations in the <a href="/en/item/managing-items#250">Linking barcodes</a> chapter.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="Mediamarkt">10.2. Activating the catalogue export</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You have set up Mediamarkt and created a catalogue for exporting your item data? Then start the export of your item data.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating the catalogue export to Mediamarkt:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Data » Catalogues</strong>.<br>
→ The catalogues are listed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Scroll to the Mediamarkt catalogue.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Active/Inactive</strong> column, move the toggle button to the right (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-toggle-on  "></i></span>).<br>
→ The catalogue is active.<br>
→ The catalogue data is exported to Mediamarkt Daily{if-active}.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="700">11. Setting the variation availability</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You need to activate all variations that you want to sell on Mediamarkt. This is done in the <strong>Availability</strong> tab of a variation within the <strong>Item » Edit item » [Open item] » Tab: Variation ID</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Use group function or batch processing</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can edit the availability of several variations at once by using either the <a href="/en/item/managing-items#100">variation group function</a> or <a href="/en/item/managing-items#400">batch processing</a>.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting the variation availability for Mediamarkt:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item » [Open item] » Tab: Variation ID » Tab: Settings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the variation that you want to sell on Mediamarkt.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To sell all variations of an item on Mediamarkt, carry out the settings for the item’s main variation. This activates the availability of all variations of the item.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Availability</strong> area, activate the option <strong>Active</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Availability</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Markets</strong> area, click in the selection field.<br>
→ A list of all available markets is displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the option <strong>Mediamarkt</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus-square  "></i></span>).<br>
→ The market is added.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The variation is available for Mediamarkt.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="480">12. Setting up event procedures</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Set up an <a href="/en/automation/event-procedures">event procedure</a> to automatically update the order status on Mediamarkt whenever specific events occur. You can set up the following event procedures:</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>How to set up the event procedures in plentymarkets is described in the following chapters.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Additional procedures</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In addition to the event procedures listed above, the Mediamarkt plugin provides several other event procedures. These procedures exist because order processing differs between plentymarkets and Mirakl.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>However, we recommend that you only use the procedures described in detail.</p>
</div>
</td>
